						<div class="postbody">I thought the point was to just copy the attributes byte into the OAM unchanged, so that's why you have the bits exactly matching up.<br />Anyway, when I was making metasprites, I had the option available to OR/XOR the attributes byte with something else, so you could easily make palette-swapped sprites.  Maybe you could handle flipped versions of sprites and stuff that way, treat the flip flag in the attributes byte as a request for a flipped version of the metasprite, and change the X/Y advance depending on flip flags.</div>

					
